stac-trace

Real-time Earth observation satellite constellation visualizer.
Shows where high-resolution imagery is being collected and why.

Live: ltrg.co.uk/stac-trace

What it does:
- Tracks 100+ EO satellites (Maxar, Airbus, Planet, Capella, ICEYE, 21AT)
- Shows live orbital positions with operator-coloured trails
- Displays 470K+ imagery footprints from the last 30 days
- Detects multi-provider overlap clusters (areas imaged by 2+ operators)
- Click a cluster: satellite basemap, Overpass POI query, Claude analysis

Data sources:
- UP42 STAC API (Airbus, Maxar, 21AT, Capella imagery metadata)
- Planet Data API (SkySat direct)
- CelesTrak (satellite TLEs)
- Overpass API (OpenStreetMap strategic features)
- Claude CLI (streaming intelligence analysis, localhost only)

Stack:
- Python (data pipeline, run with uv)
- DuckDB + GeoParquet (storage and delivery)
- MapLibre GL JS (globe visualisation)
- satellite.js (SGP4 orbital propagation)
- duckdb-wasm (client-side parquet queries)
- Vanilla JS/CSS (no build step)

Run locally:
  uv run scripts/fetch_tles.py
  uv run scripts/sync_stac.py --days 30
  uv run scripts/sync_planet.py
  uv run scripts/export_parquet.py
  cd web && ln -s ../data data && cd ..
  uv run serve.py

Requires .env with UP42_USERNAME, UP42_PASSWORD, PLANET_API_KEY.
Claude analysis requires an authenticated claude CLI (Max subscription).

Daily sync via GitHub Actions. Deployed to GitHub Pages.
